  "description": "In another babble I talked about Moscow-school semiotics, and how it might describe more than just one of my paracosmic worlds, and am now thinking about what a world made from Moscow-school semiotics might look like. I\u0026rsquo;m not sure the literature itself is the best for laying out the structure of such a world, though, at least not in an easy-to-convert-into-code form. Nevertheless, it seems worth trying as a general concept.\nTo start with, I\u0026rsquo;m ignoring skinning, and asking, what structure do the interactions between the player and the world need to have, for those interactions to be describable as within the semiosphere, a world described by Moscow-school semiotics?\n",
  "name": "2025-09-16, 1825h, Drafting moscow semiotics in fennel",
